<tr>
<td vAlign='absmiddle' align='left' width='80%' colSpan='4' bgcolor='#000000' class='header'><img border='0' src='./images/cricon.gif' align='absmiddle'> FIERY DEFENDER</td>
</tr>
<tr> 
<td width='80%'><body>

<p>Fiery Defender</p>
<p>Irak Altil is a named skeleton in fear, that after following a line of
questioning brings this up:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START-->
<i>You say, 'what sword?'<br>
Irak Altil says 'Hands of a twisted brother no longer living.<br>
<br>
You say, 'what shield'<br>
Irak Altil says 'Earthly children of the god of hate. Keeping stand over his
dark brothers and sisters.<br>
<br>
You say, 'what breastplate'<br>
Irak Altil lets loose an unearthly howl as it gleams with sickly light. 'Upon
she who lured me from my post. In that place where hatred festers. Painful
corruption.' </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START-->
<b>The sword</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->
 is found in The Hole off a mob named &quot;Keeper of the Tombs&quot;. Spawntime
has been reported to be between 7 and 10 days. Bring at least 3 groups to take
this guy down. Here's a map to The Hole(Thanks Andorion):<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START-->
<a href="http://www.bol.ucla.edu/~berjd/hole/">www.bol.ucla.edu/~berjd/hole/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END-->
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START-->
<b>The shield </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->
is found on Kirik Vil in Nektulos Forest, and can be handled by 2 groups since
you get him alone. Just bring alot of petcasters/tanks to take him down faster
than his regen can handle. No reportings if Disease Cloud stuck on him, but if
it does it would sure help with the regen. Use the log at 1500,-800 for your
group to pull to, he should roam by in sight on the northwest side of you on
regular intervals. Spawntime has also here been reported to be between 7 and 10
days.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START-->
<b>The breastplate</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->
 is off Thought Destroyers in hate. Last four times I've went two has spawned
three times and 3 the fourth. They spawn sometimes after you kill a banshee -
right at the spot where the banshee dies. Level 55ish and shouldn't be a problem
to handle for any group of people doing hate.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START-->
<i>Irak Altil says 'The sword must be dipped in water pure. Light of clean
spirit to cleanse the shield. A gem of clarity unlike any other for the
breastplate. All must be cleansed and returned to the temple for my soul to be
freed. Only the temple can cleanse, only they can touch the artifacts. Take the
sets of two to the temple. When they are all three cleansed seperately take them
to he who will grant me atonement.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START-->
<b>The shield</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->
 is to be turned in alone to Elia the Pure, she has the reagent herself. You
will then recieve a &quot;Gleaming Crested Shield&quot;.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START-->
<b>The sword's</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->
 reagent is found in West Freeport. Find the Peasant Woman and tell her 'I will
take it'. Give it to her brother Joshua that's in the closest house from the
Woman and you get &quot;a bucket of pure water&quot; which identifies as
&quot;Blessed by Sacrifice&quot;.<br>
Now turn the sword and the water in to Reklon Gnallen in the Peacekeepers guild
in Erudin. You will then recieve a &quot;Gleaming Crested Sword&quot;.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START-->
<b>The breastplate's</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->
 gem is in Kaladim. Find Jark in the mines below the bank, hail him and say
'some'. Proceed with the dialogue and finally tell him the keyword 'dinner' or
some other. Follow his instructions and bring him his dinner. Nella, his wife,
can be found at the crystals(wishing pond) right in front of the temple(pal/clr
guild). I'm told the keyword 'dinner' spawns her. Hail her and say 'dinner'.
Bring the item back to him and you get &quot;Pure Crystal&quot; which identifies
as &quot;Blessed by Compassion&quot;.<br>
Now take both the Crystal and the Breastplate to Reklon Gnallen in the
Peacekeepers guild in Erudin. You will recieve a &quot;Gleaming Crested
Breastplate&quot;.<br>
<br>
Turn the three cleansed items(Gleaming Crested pieces) back to Reklon, he will
hand you a &quot;mark of atonement&quot;. He also states:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START-->
<i>Reklon Gnallen says 'I never thought our order would see these artifacts
again. With the return of these relics we can now put at ease a scar upon the
history of our order. This cleansing will atone for his failure. Your soul must
be pure to have given so freely of yourself. Go now, take this crested token of
our order. If you wish to free his soul you must undertake another sacrifice.<br>
<br>
You say, 'what sacrifice'<br>
Reklon Gnallen says 'Only this crest and the sacrifice of something that
symbolizes your strength and purity will release his spirit into the cleansing
flames of our lady Quellious. Go now. Thank you Soandso . </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->
<br>
<br>
<br>
Next step is to bring your Fiery Avenger and the Mark of Atonement to Irak Altil.
He now spawns when you kill one of the golems (Fright reports seem to state),
and will despawn within an hour or so SO MOVE FAST and leave fright for as long
as possible (possibly right before cazic, if he's up too). Turn them in and you
recieve your new toy:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START-->
<i>Fiery Defender<br>
2hs 35/40<br>
effect: holy shock (150 dd stun!)<br>
15ac 20str 10sta 15wis 70hp 30mana<br>
and +10 to all resists</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->
<br>
<br>
<br>
Thank you Khael</p>

</body></td>
